                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18491126-name-895" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-895" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-895" type="surname" value="MCCLELLAND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-895" type="given" value="HUGH"></interp>HUGH MCCLELLAND</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a corporal of artillery—the prisoner was gunner in the same corps, and occupied the same room as me. On 22d Nov., at half-past eight o'clock in the morning, I left my quarters, leaving my watch and guard, and eight or ten shillings safe in my box, which was locked, and I kept the key—the prisoner was there when I left—I came back, between ten and eleven—the prisoner was gone—he ought to have stayed to take care of the room—my box was broken open, and I missed my watch and money; this is the watch (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>)—the prisoner never came back, but was appre<lb></lb>hended by the police.</p>
